<TITLE> Bayern's Ribery ruled out of Champions League final </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ZURICH, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Bayern Munich playmaker Franck Ribery will miss the Champions League final after he was handed a three-match suspension by UEFA on Wednesday. Ribery was sent off for serious foul play in the first leg of Bayern's semi-final victory over Olympique Lyon, and European soccer's ruling body has confirmed he will be banned for three games. Ribery did not play in the second leg of the semi-final in Lyon on Tuesday which Bayern won 3-0 to complete a 4-0 aggregate victory. The German side, who have three days to appeal against the decision, will play either Barcelona or Inter Milan in the final on May 22 in Ma
